dagster-io/dagster#30241.body:
### What's the issue or suggestion?

In the documentation for loading singular dbt tests as asset checks, the example `meta.dagster.ref` block uses the field `package_name`:

```
{{
    config(
        meta={
            'dagster': {
                'ref': {
                    'name': 'customers',
                    'package_name': 'my_dbt_assets',
                    'version': 1,
                },
            }
        }
    )
}}
```

https://docs.dagster.io/integrations/libraries/dbt/reference#singular-tests

However, the actual Dagster code that processes this reference expects the field to be named `package` instead of `package_name`. This causes the lookup to silently fail and the asset check is not attached as expected.

https://github.com/dagster-io/dagster/blob/c81d66db57b048a14db90f6dde2b5cdd9961e80f/python_modules/libraries/dagster-dbt/dagster_dbt/asset_utils.py#L892

Once `package` is used, the check is attached as expected.

